The paper deals with deep learning for medical image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a multi-scale convolutional layer and a top-k pooling technique, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of weak annotations and multiple instance learning (MIL) is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of neural networks for classification, which is a subfield of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
